title: Test: Navigate with Post-Navigate Actions
tags: 
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

This test demonstrates the new post-navigate actions feature.

!! Test 1: Basic navigation with focus action

<$button>
<$action-navigate $to="TestTarget" $actions="""<$action-sendmessage $message="tm-focus-selector" $param=".tc-tiddler-title"/>"""/>
Navigate and Focus Title
</$button>

!! Test 2: Navigation with multiple actions

<$button>
<$action-navigate $to="TestTarget" $actions="""
<$action-log $$message="Post-navigate actions executed!"/>
<$action-sendmessage $message="tm-focus-selector" $param=".tc-tiddler-body"/>
"""/>
Navigate and Execute Multiple Actions
</$button>

!! Test 3: Using tm-navigate message directly

<$button message="tm-navigate" param="TestTarget">
<$action-setfield $tiddler="$:/temp/navigate-test" text="Action executed after navigate"/>
Navigate (Direct Message - No Actions Yet)
</$button>

---

<<.tip "The post-navigate actions are executed after the DOM has been refreshed, making it possible to focus elements that are only available after the navigation refresh.">>
